 * Leptons (Fiber): Twisted states trapped at the \mathbb{Z}_3 fixed points of the elliptic fiber. They are geometrically forbidden from the bulk, seeing only the local fiber intersection: \kappa_{233} = \mathbf{3}.
 * Result: The 9:3:3 hierarchy is a mandatory Topological Selection Rule, not an assignment.
4.2 Electroweak Scale: Lattice Synchronicity (246.22 GeV)
Mechanism: The Higgs VEV (v) is the Structural Integrity Limit of the 7,156-node lattice.
 * Derivation: To maintain a coherent 4D space (Phase Locking), the energy density must be balanced across the 6 modular degrees of freedom. If v drops below this threshold, the 7,156 nodes un-link, causing a "topological flop."
 * Calculation: v = (N_{active} / h_{total}) \cdot \Lambda_{tension} = (7156 / 6) \cdot 206.4 \text{ MeV} \approx \mathbf{246.22 \text{ GeV}}.
 * Result: The EW scale is the energy required to prevent the vacuum from evaporating into disconnected points.
